    <div class="wrap grid">
      <section class="panel" aria-label="Attorney invite overview">
        <h2>What you’re inviting them to review</h2>
        <p>
          SharpeSystem is being built as a structured orientation layer: decision trees, scope notices, and disciplined process prompts that
          reduce procedural drift and improve the quality of client-provided information.
        </p>

        <div class="hr"></div>

        <h2>Why attorneys might care</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cleaner intake:</strong> fewer scattered narratives, more structured facts.</li>
          <li><strong>Lower friction:</strong> clients stop re-litigating basics and start answering the right questions.</li>
          <li><strong>Better documentation:</strong> consistent, time-stamped, audit-friendly “what happened / what’s next.”</li>
          <li><strong>Boundary clarity:</strong> pages are explicitly non-advice and non-directive.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="note">
          <strong>Positioning rule:</strong> you are not asking them to “use your system” yet.
          You’re inviting them to <em>view the concept</em> and optionally give feedback.
        </div>

        <div class="hr"></div>

        <h2>Suggested pages to include</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/high-conflict-risk-awareness.html">Risk Awareness</a> — neutral education, professional tone.</li>
          <li><a href="/trees.html">Decision Trees</a> — the orientation “index.”</li>
          <li><a href="/status.html">Status</a> — the scope boundary in plain English.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="footer">
          <div><strong>Reminder:</strong> This site provides general orientation only. No legal advice. No representation. No attorney-client relationship.</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <aside class="mini" aria-label="Copy invite message">
        <h2>Copy an invite message</h2>
        <p>
          Keep it calm and low-pressure. The objective is to get a serious attorney to click a link without triggering spam instincts.
        </p>

        <div class="pill-row" aria-label="Tags">
          <span class="pill">Low-pressure</span>
